ble: `sm`, `md` (default), and `lg`."},"756":{"id":"/docs/components/segmented-controller-23","page_id":"/docs/components/segmented-controller","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/segmented-controller#icon--text","content":"Segments can include an `Icon` alongside text for added visual context."},"757":{"id":"/docs/components/segmented-controller-24","page_id":"/docs/components/segmented-controller","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/segmented-controller#icon-only","content":"For compact layouts, segments can contain only icons. Provide an `aria-label` on each item so screen readers can identify the action."},"758":{"id":"/docs/components/segmented-controller-25","page_id":"/docs/components/segmented-controller","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/segmented-controller#overflow","content":"When the number of options exceeds the width of the container, the component automatically shows scroll buttons to let users navigate. Users can also scroll horizontally to navigate the options."},"759":{"id":"/docs/components/segmented-controller-26","page_id":"/docs/components/segmented-controller","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/segmented-controller#rtl-direction","content":"The segmented controller follows the current **layout direction** (LTR or RTL). By default, that direction is detected automatically from the browser or system settings."},"760":{"id":"/docs/components/segmented-controller-27","page_id":"/docs/components/segmented-controller","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/segmented-controller#disabled-states","content":"Disable the entire group with `isDisabled` on the container, or disable individual segments with `isDisabled` on specific items."},"761":{"id":"/docs/components/segmented-controller-28","page_id":"/docs/components/segmented-controller","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/segmented-controller#data-attributes","content":"Components automatically add data attributes for styling di